:"1377.","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"cs":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie"},"da":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"nl":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Yelverton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon): habitational name from either of two places called Yelverton, in Norfolk or Devon. Medieval examples of the surname are from the Norfolk place, but the modern surname in Britain is associated mainly with Devon, where the earliest record of the surname is found in 1761, and is probably a substitution for   Elford  , an earlier form of the Devon placename. The Devon place, a hamlet in Buckland Monachorum, is not officially on record as <i>Yelverton</i> until the 19th century, when the Great Western Railway so named the station it built there in 1859. It is a dialect pronunciation of <i>Elverton</i>, which is first recorded in 1765 as an extended form of its medieval name <i>Elford</i> + <i>-ton</i> ‘town’. The Norfolk placename is recorded as <i>Ailuertuna</i> in 1086, and probably derives from the Old English personal name <i>Æthelfrith</i> or <i>Geldfrith</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Elford","meanings":["English: habitational name from Yelverton in Buckland Monachorum (Devon), recorded as <i>Elleford</i> in 1291 (see   Yelverton  ), named from the Old English personal name <i>Ella</i> or <i>elle</i>, <i>ellen</i> ‘elder tree’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. The name may also derive from any of the places called Elford in Staffordshire and Northumberland, both probably from the Old English personal name <i>Ella</i> + <i>ford</i>."]},{"name":"Yelvington","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Yelverton  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Robert Yelverton Esquire was born in 1327, in Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Andrew de Yelverton, was 28 and his mother, Margaret de Boson, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Cecily Bardolf. He died in 1377, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Robert Yelverton Esquire est né en 1327, à Rackheath, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Andrew de Yelverton, avait 28 ans et sa mère, Margaret de Boson, avait 24 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Cecily Bardolf. Il est décédé en 1377, à Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 50 ans."},"de":{"1327–1377":"1327–1377","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1355–1408":"1355–1408","1300–1383":"1300–1383","1304–1327":"1304–1327","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1324":"1324","1355":"1355","1377":"1377","1300":"1300","1386":"1386","1383":"1383","1408":"1408","Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rackheath, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Whissonsett, Norfolk, England":"Whissonsett, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"